132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1461
H.P. 953 House of Representatives, April 3, 2025
An Act to Prohibit School Boards from Implementing or Enforcing
Mask Mandates
Reference to the Committee on Education and Cultural Affairs suggested and ordered
printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative EDER of Waterboro.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA ยง6558 is enacted to read:
3 ยง6558. Prohibition on mask mandates
4 1. Mask mandate; definition. As used in this section, "mask mandate" means any
5 requirement imposed by a school board requiring the wearing of a medical or nonmedical
6 face mask by a student, staff member or visitor within a school facility or during a school-
7 related activity.
8 2. Prohibition. A school board may not implement or enforce a policy that requires a
9 school administrative unit to adopt a mask mandate.
10 3. Enforcement. The department shall oversee the compliance of the provisions of
11 this section and ensure that school boards adhere to the prohibition under this section.
12 4. Penalties. A school board that violates this section is subject to penalties as
13 determined by the department, which may include the withholding of state funds allocated
14 to the school administrative unit that the school board governs.
15 SUMMARY
1166 This bill prohibits a school board from implementing or enforcing a policy that requires
1177 a school administrative unit to adopt a mask mandate.
